"{\"uid\": \"vogue.com-article-olympic-diver-tom-daley-confirms-his-retirement\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Tom Daley-the 30-year-old British diver who, remarkably, has competed in fiveOlympic Games-is officially retiring.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 26, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9777603009485611, \"rank\": 0.02151272937899496, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tom Daley\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 9}, {\"ngram\": \"fiveOlympic Games\", \"from\": 73, \"to\": 90}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The news arrives on the heels of a stellar final showing in Paris: Alongside diving partner Noah Williams, Daley nabbed silver in the men's 10-meter synchronized platform.\", \"from\": 116, \"to\": 287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 176, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2465056080349753e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 208, \"end\": 221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"score\": 0.9999982736077423, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Williams_(diver)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The news\", \"from\": 116, \"to\": 124}, {\"ngram\": \"the heels\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 145}, {\"ngram\": \"a stellar final showing\", \"from\": 149, \"to\": 172}, {\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 228}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 10-meter synchronized platform\", \"from\": 246, \"to\": 286}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The medal, Daley's fifth after bronzes in London and Rio de Janeiro, plus a gold and a bronze in Tokyo, was more than just his last: It meant he'd \\\"completed the colors,\\\" he tells me with a grin.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.13878704274848e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.438506797266183e-23, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 385, \"end\": 390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999968918066872, \"rank\": 3.105463569520652e-06, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medal\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 297}, {\"ngram\": \"bronzes\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 368}, {\"ngram\": \"a bronze\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"the colors\", \"from\": 446, \"to\": 456}, {\"ngram\": \"a grin\", \"from\": 476, \"to\": 482}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Another feather in his Paris cap: He was chosen as a flag bearer for Great Britain during the riverineopening ceremony.)\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 508, \"end\": 513, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2465056080349753e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 567, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9996559623987695, \"rank\": 0.00034242492739909087, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a flag bearer\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"the riverineopening ceremony\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 603}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are sitting in an anteroom at Soho House Paris, where Daley has met with me-extremely punctually, it's worth noting; he appeared at 2:00 p.m. on the dot-to discuss his milestone news and exemplary career.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 814, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2465056080349753e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an anteroom\", \"from\": 625, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 669}, {\"ngram\": \"2:00 p.m.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"the dot\", \"from\": 755, \"to\": 762}, {\"ngram\": \"his milestone news\", \"from\": 774, \"to\": 792}, {\"ngram\": \"exemplary career\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It feels very, very surreal,\\\" he says.\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I felt so incredibly nervous going into this, knowing it was my last Olympics.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 935, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my last Olympics\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a lot of pressure and expectation.\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 951}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"expectation\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was eager for it to be done\\u2026 but when I walked out, and saw my husband [Lance] and kids [Robbie and Phoenix] and my friends and family in the audience, I was like, You know what?\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1161, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my husband\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1053}, {\"ngram\": \"kids\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1070}, {\"ngram\": \"the audience\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is exactly why I did this.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am here, and no matter what happens in the competition itself, I am going to be happy.\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1282, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was emotional at the end, up there on the platform, knowing it was going to be my last competitive dive,\\\" he continues.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1407, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1305, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the platform\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1338}, {\"ngram\": \"my last competitive dive\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I have to make the decision at some point, and it feels like the right time.\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"some point\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1454}, {\"ngram\": \"the right time\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1488}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the right time to call it a day.\\\"\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1528, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the right time\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1509}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, Daley, who was born in Plymouth, Great Britain, in 1994, has been diving since just about the turn of the millennium.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plymouth\", \"score\": 0.9999999995634425, \"rank\": 4.3671538434155326e-10, \"text\": \"Plymouth\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plymouth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plymouth\"}, {\"begin\": 1574, \"end\": 1587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9996559623987695, \"rank\": 0.00034242492739909087, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"the turn\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the millennium\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1657}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He qualified for his first Games at the age of 14, competing in Beijing in 2008.\", \"from\": 1659, \"to\": 1739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1723, \"end\": 1730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9856717965634813, \"rank\": 0.014536485121420285, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his first Games\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"the age\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There, Daley's father, Robert Daley-who was deeply involved in and supportive of his son's early career-was able to watch Tom compete.\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley's father\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"Robert Daley\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"his son's early career\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1843}, {\"ngram\": \"Tom compete\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Robert would die from brain cancer three years later.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1932, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Robert\", \"from\": 1879, \"to\": 1885}, {\"ngram\": \"brain cancer\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1913}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ever since, Daley's mother, Debbie, has remained a fixture at his events; in Paris, she could be seen cheering in the stands with Lance and her grandchildren.\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 2091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1961, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Debbie_Dingle\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2420153242582882e-11, \"text\": \"Debbie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Debbie_Dingle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Debbie_Dingle\"}, {\"begin\": 2010, \"end\": 2015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2465056080349753e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley's mother\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"a fixture\", \"from\": 1982, \"to\": 1991}, {\"ngram\": \"his events\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"the stands\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2057}, {\"ngram\": \"Lance\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2068}, {\"ngram\": \"her grandchildren\", \"from\": 2073, \"to\": 2090}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley's mother, Debbie, his children, and his husband, Lance, in the stands during the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2109, \"end\": 2115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Debbie_Dingle\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2420153242582882e-11, \"text\": \"Debbie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Debbie_Dingle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Debbie_Dingle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley's mother\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2107}, {\"ngram\": \"his children\", \"from\": 2117, \"to\": 2129}, {\"ngram\": \"his husband\", \"from\": 2135, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"Lance\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2153}, {\"ngram\": \"the stands\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2168}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley made global headlines when he came out as gay, via a YouTube video, in 2013.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2253, \"end\": 2260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.112502236897951e-13, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"global headlines\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2221}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He felt it was necessary after a tabloid splashed out a baseless headline reading: \\\"Tom Daley, 'I am Not Gay.'\\\"\", \"from\": 2277, \"to\": 2388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tabloid\", \"from\": 2308, \"to\": 2317}, {\"ngram\": \"a baseless headline reading\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2358}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(At that point, he had neither directly denied nor confirmed his sexuality publicly.)\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2474, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"his sexuality\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2463}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It infuriated me that somebody would say that.\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2522, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"somebody\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I never wanted to be seen as lying or hiding from who I was,\\\" Daley says.\", \"from\": 2523, \"to\": 2596, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is pleased to see that now, \\\"with every Olympics, there are more and more out athletes\\\"-a big difference from a decade ago.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2724, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every Olympics\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"more and more out athletes\\\"-a big difference\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2705}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's powerful.\\\"\", \"from\": 2725, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he also knows well the specific, occasionally unwelcome responsbilities that come with representation.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2848, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the specific, occasionally unwelcome responsbilities\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"representation\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2847}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think there is a lot of pressure for when people do come out to be an activist and to be outspoken.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2872}, {\"ngram\": \"pressure\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2900}, {\"ngram\": \"an activist\", \"from\": 2919, \"to\": 2930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And sometimes that's just not in some people's nature,\\\" he says.\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 3016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some people's nature\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think this might be part of the reason why possibly more people have not felt as comfortable with coming out.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3040, \"to\": 3044}, {\"ngram\": \"the reason\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3058}, {\"ngram\": \"possibly more people\", \"from\": 3063, \"to\": 3083}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I also think that [the world of sport] is such a heteronormative space\\u2026 lots of queer kids, when they are younger, have this automatic feeling that they should not fit into sports, so they do not pursue them.\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3338, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3162, \"to\": 3167}, {\"ngram\": \"such a heteronormative space\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3200}, {\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 3202, \"to\": 3206}, {\"ngram\": \"queer kids\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3220}, {\"ngram\": \"this automatic feeling\", \"from\": 3250, \"to\": 3272}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I hope we will see more in the future.\\\"\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3378, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3376}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley says that, back before that headline was written, he'd been asked why he thought he had such a large gay following.\", \"from\": 3380, \"to\": 3501, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 3380, \"to\": 3385}, {\"ngram\": \"that headline\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3422}, {\"ngram\": \"such a large gay following\", \"from\": 3474, \"to\": 3500}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He replied, \\\"Probably because I am half-naked all the time.\\\"\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3562, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These days, his personal audience now reaches north of five million followers.\", \"from\": 3563, \"to\": 3641, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his personal audience\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3596}, {\"ngram\": \"five million followers\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus, being a high-profile diver is instant internet catnip-their events are fast-paced and dazzling, ready-made for TikToks and Reels-and Daley is confident and knowingly playfulin his digital presence.\", \"from\": 3643, \"to\": 3846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3760, \"end\": 3767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"TikToks\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TikTok\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a high-profile diver\", \"from\": 3655, \"to\": 3675}, {\"ngram\": \"instant internet catnip\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3702}, {\"ngram\": \"their events\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3715}, {\"ngram\": \"Reels\", \"from\": 3772, \"to\": 3777}, {\"ngram\": \"Daley\", \"from\": 3782, \"to\": 3787}, {\"ngram\": \"his digital presence\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3845}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He seems very comfortable in his own skin.\", \"from\": 3847, \"to\": 3889, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his own skin\", \"from\": 3876, \"to\": 3888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Really,\\\" he says, laughing, \\\"being in trunks all of the time, that's my work attire.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3978, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"trunks\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 3938}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 3946, \"to\": 3954}, {\"ngram\": \"my work attire\", \"from\": 3963, \"to\": 3977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are not many people that wear more clothes to bed than they do to work.\\\"\", \"from\": 3979, \"to\": 4057, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 3993, \"to\": 4004}, {\"ngram\": \"more clothes\", \"from\": 4015, \"to\": 4027}, {\"ngram\": \"bed\", \"from\": 4031, \"to\": 4034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We shift away from the conference room at this point in our chat, and head upstairs to Soho House's terrace.\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4146, \"end\": 4156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soho_House\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0309768891394064e-26, \"text\": \"Soho House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soho_House\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soho_House\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 